result.name: Fukuro

reviews.text:
A Japanese restaurant by name, it serves fusion dishes. Presentation is fancy like contemporary art. Good for photos for sure if you’re looking for some materials for your instagram.  But the ingredients, for this price range, it could be better(fresher). 
It is quite a popular restaurant so be prepared to wait in queue for a (long) while. Waiting prolongs even when you’re seating...good place to kill time passively. Inspiring place for whining.
No bookings and if your unlucky the wait can be long.  Great ambiance and vibe, yummy food the wagyu beef and the prawns we're a stand out.  Service was friendly and attentive, bit not over the top.

Overall Experience was good, Food was excellent and the lively vibe of the restaurant is one to remember. However, the waiter serving us might need additional training. We asked for a "good" sake as there was so much to choose from. Instead of asking us what we liked he went ahead and asked us to define "good" in a patronizing tone of voice. I didn't speak of it at the moment as I was with a date and didn't want to be rude, but I thought to myself how unprofessional of him to respond in such a way. Other than this incident, the rest of the meal was decent. Taste and presentation of the food was better than what I expected. However, waiter's attitude was totally off-putting. Might not be a second visit :/
Tapas dishes were unreal. Found the vibe to be really unique. Cool drink options.
Fukuro is a guarantee of great food, service and a great time. My personal favorite is the yaki udon 🥰
